{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17625484","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17625484"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T16:25:14+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T16:25:14+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17029"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17029","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17029"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.22,0.51,0.07,0.04,0.16]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9719"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76202"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9719","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9719"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17029"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61706"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"1"},{"type":"tags","id":"5"},{"type":"tags","id":"44"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"181"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4938"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"5224"},{"type":"tags","id":"5225"},{"type":"tags","id":"5784"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"22866"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22871"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76202","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/76202"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 56-year-old woman with cirrhosis presents with severe cancer pain. Her liver function tests show:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003EBilirubin: 65 \u03bcmol/L (3-20)\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EAlbumin: 28 g/L (35-50)\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EALT: 85 U/L (5-40)\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EALP: 280 U/L (30-110)\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EINR: 1.8 (0.9-1.2)\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes why hydromorphone might be preferred over morphine in this patient?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Fewer active metabolites","It is not metabolised in the liver","More rapid onset of action","Lower risk of respiratory depression","Half-life in cirrhosis is significantly more prolonged"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFewer active metabolites\u003C/strong\u003E than morphine makes hydromorphone a safer choice in cirrhotic patients. Most cirrhotic patients have vulnerable or impaired renal function, leading to a build up of morphine\u0027s toxic metabolites with deleterious consequences.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGreater first-pass metabolism\u003C/strong\u003E - Hydromorphone actually undergoes less first-pass metabolism than morphine\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIt is not metabolised in the liver \u003C/strong\u003E- Hydromorphone is metabolised in the liver via glucuronidation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELower risk of respiratory depression\u003C/strong\u003E - Hydromorphone can still cause significant respiratory depression\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHalf life in cirrhosis is significantly more prolonged\u003C/strong\u003E - Incorrect, morphine\u0027s half life is significantly more prolonged in cirrhosis than that of hydromorphone, making dosing more challenging. This is another reason why hydromorphone is preferable.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIn cirrhotic patients, the half life of morphine is significantly affected and the potential for accumulation of its toxic metabolites is increased, making it an undesirable opioid in this population.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["In cirrhotic patients, the half-life of hydromorphone is less affected than the half-life of morphine, which is significantly prolonged.","Hydromorphone is metabolised in the liver, but has fewer active metabolites than morphine, making it safer in cirrhotic patients.","Hydromorphone is approximately 5 times more potent than morphine and produces fewer active metabolites."],"references":["Ritter J, Flower RJ (Rod J), Henderson G (Graeme), et al.\u00a0Rang and Dale\u2019s Pharmacology. Tenth edition. Elsevier; 2024.","Chandok N, Watt KD. Pain management in the cirrhotic patient: the clinical challenge. Mayo Clin Proc. 2010;85(5):451-458. doi:10.4065/mcp.2009.0534","Rakoski M, Goyal P, Spencer-Safier M, Weissman J, Mohr G, Volk M. Pain management in patients with cirrhosis. Clin Liver Dis (Hoboken). 2018;11(6):135-140. Published 2018 Jul 26. doi:10.1002/cld.711"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61706"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17029"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61706","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/61706"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-02T12:31:10+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-02T12:31:37+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9719"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76202"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"1","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/1"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude34","name":"Anaesthesia","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"5"}}},"meta":